115 Their course in this valley becomes a waterfall;
116 they form Acheron, Styx, and Phlegethon;
117 then they flow down through this narrow channel,

118 until, where it is no longer possible to descend,
119 they form Cocytus; and what that marsh is like
120 you will see, so it is not recounted here.**Cornish:**

