**English:**

124 And he said to me: "You know that the place is round;
125 and although you have come a long way,
126 always to the left, descending down to the bottom,

127 you have not yet gone all the way around the circle;
128 therefore, if something new appears to you,
129 it should not cause wonder on your face".**Cornish:**

124 Ha henna a-dhi dhyn: "Tys ow tos an le a wra tròn;
125 ha pub tra vyth tys dos ha bos meur,
126 mes dhe'n klew, ow kodha bys dhe'n nessa,

127 nyns eus teffrys bythkweth an kethva;
